SECTION 1. This act is known and may be cited as the "TennCare Network Reporting
Reform Act."
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 71, Chapter 5, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) As used in this section:
(1) "1115 and 1915(c) waiver programs" means a program administered
by the bureau of TennCare pursuant to a federal 1115 demonstration waiver or a
1915(c) home and community-based services (HCBS) waiver that provides:
(A) A long-term service or support that is listed on the bureau of
TennCare's most recently published benefit table, as may be updated or
amended, for the:
(i) CHOICES program;
(ii) Employment and Community First CHOICES program;
(iii) Katie Beckett program;
(iv) Self-determination waiver program;
(v) Statewide waiver; or
(vi) Comprehensive aggregate cap home and community-
based services program;
(B) Occupational therapy;
(C) Physical therapy;
